Sentencas: Solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) membranes were developed in which zirconia-based electrolyte thin films were supported by a porous composite metal/ceramic current collector and were subjected to rapid thermal cycling between 475 and 1075 K (200 and 800 degreesC).
Titulo: Metal-supported solid oxide fuel cell membranes for rapid thermal cycling

Sentencas: The effects of this cycling on membrane performance were evaluated.
Titulo: Metal-supported solid oxide fuel cell membranes for rapid thermal cycling

Sentencas: The membranes, not yet optimized for performance, showed a peak power density of 350 mW/cm(2) at 1175 K (900 degreesC) in laboratory-sized SOFCs, while rapid thermal cycling had only a marginal effect on cell performance.
Titulo: Metal-supported solid oxide fuel cell membranes for rapid thermal cycling

Sentencas: This resistance to cycling degradation is attributed to the close matching of thermal expansion coefficient of the porous cermet supporting current collector (PCC) with that of the zirconia electrolyte.
Titulo: Metal-supported solid oxide fuel cell membranes for rapid thermal cycling
